Subject: [PATCH] entity_reference_revisions: Guard against empty bundles in
 generateSampleValue() to avoid PHP 8+ ValueError from array_rand()

Problem
-------
In some configurations (e.g., during Devel Generate or Schema.org starterkit
content generation), there may be no referenceable bundles for an
entity_reference_revisions field. The method
EntityReferenceRevisionsItem::generateSampleValue() called array_rand($bundles)
without ensuring $bundles was non-empty, causing a PHP 8+ ValueError:
  ValueError: array_rand(): Argument #1 ($array) cannot be empty

Fix
---
Add a minimal guard that returns NULL when $bundles is empty before calling
array_rand(). This makes sample value generation skip gracefully.

--- a/public_html/modules/contrib/entity_reference_revisions/src/Plugin/Field/FieldType/EntityReferenceRevisionsItem.php
+++ b/public_html/modules/contrib/entity_reference_revisions/src/Plugin/Field/FieldType/EntityReferenceRevisionsItem.php
@@ -485,6 +485,13 @@
     else {
       $bundles = $bundle_manager->getBundleInfo($target_type_id);
     }
+
+    // In some configurations, there may be no referenceable bundles. Avoid
+    // calling array_rand() on an empty array (PHP 8+ ValueError).
+    if (empty($bundles)) {
+      return NULL;
+    }
+
     $bundle = array_rand($bundles);

     $label = NULL;
